> All runtimes but MSIE (unless they&#x27;ve added it in IE11) already implement `const`, and it&#x27;s standardized in ES6.<p>const implemented currently is very weird thing. It&#x27;s more or less a read only variable, which silently ignores updates<p>var i = 0;
for (var j = 0; j < 10; j++) {
  const C = i++;
}
// i == 10, C == 0 here<p>This is not something one would expect of constants honestly.<p>> You mean, something like ES6&#x27;s yield?<p>yield is shallow, caller must be ready to cope with yielding explicitly, so it&#x27;s not really a good replacement to proper 
coroutines that can pause arbitrary deep stacks.
